  "description": "<i>Tales from Heaven</i> is a 3D varied-viewpoint platformer resembling things like <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Mario+64\">Mario 64</a> and <a id=\"d465091bd6aaaa55bca8344865bec2cda\" href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Pandemonium\">Pandemonium</a>,  with over 2000 polygons on screen at a time, and morphing and transparency effects. In <i>Tales From Heaven</i> you play as Zak, who must chase after his beloved cat, not only for his own benefit but also to retrieve a sacred talisman required to save a land above the clouds.<br><br>Your main weapon to progress through the 12 levels are a supply of bombs, of which more can be collected as you play. These have a 3-second delay and can hurt you if you don't retreat. Many creatures can be killed by jumping on their heads. To help performance on slower systems, lo-res graphics are available and the background graphics are optional.",
